name: TENET
description: A tool for reconstructing Transfer Entropy-based causal gene NETwork from pseudo-time ordered single cell transcriptomic data
author: admin

name: FastTENET
description: FastTENET is an accelerated TENET algorithm based on manycore computing.
author: admin

name: Scribe
description: Scribe is a toolkit for detecting and visualizing causal gene regulations using Restricted Directed Information, leveraging time-delayed information transfer.
author: admin

name: FastSCODE
description: FastSCODE: an accelerated implementation of SCODE based on manycore computing
author: admin

name: LEAP
description: LEAP is a tool for constructing gene co-expression networks from single-cell RNA-seq data using pseudotime-based time-lagged correlations.
author: admin

name: GENIE3
description: GENIE3 is a machine learning-based tool that infers gene regulatory networks from expression data using tree-based methods.
author: admin

name: GRNBOOST2
description: GRNBoost2 is a scalable tool for gene regulatory network inference inspired by GENIE3.
author: admin
